---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Privacy Policy - Perfect Pace";
const description = "Privacy Policy for Perfect Pace. Learn how we handle your data and cookies.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mx-auto py-8">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Welcome to Perfect Pace. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data.
            This privacy policy will inform you as to how we look after your personal data when you visit our website
            and tell you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>
            Currently, Perfect Pace operates primarily as a client-side application. This means:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>We do not store your race plans, splits, or personal settings on our servers.</li>
            <li>All your planning data remains on your device.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
            We use "Local Storage" and may use cookies to improve your experience.
        </p>

        <h3>Essential Local Storage</h3>
        <p>
            We use local storage to remember your preferences, such as:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Theme Preference:</strong> To remember if you prefer Dark Mode or Light Mode.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> To remember your choices regarding cookies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics Cookies (Optional)</h3>
        <p>
            We may use third-party analytics tools (like Google Analytics) to help us understand how our website is used.
            These tools use cookies to collect anonymous information about website traffic and user behavior.
            You can choose to enable or disable these cookies via our Cookie Banner settings at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
            Under GDPR and other privacy laws, you have rights regarding your data. Since we do not store personal data
            on our servers, you have full control over the data stored in your browser. You can clear your browser's
            cache and local storage at any time to remove this data.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us.
        </p>
    </div>
</Layout>
